<h1 >Guide to Social Security Law Updates - 2000</h1>
<ul><li><a href="2000#27november2000">27 November 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#30october2000">30 October 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#20september2000">20 September 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#28august2000">28 August 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#31july2000">31 July 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#3july2000">3 July 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#29may2000">29 May 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#1may2000">1 May 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#27march2000">27 March 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#28february2000">28 February 2000</a></li>
<li><a href="2000#31january2000">31 January 2000</a></li>
</ul><h2 id="27november2000">Guide to Social Security Law Update 1450G # Date 27 November 2000</h2>
<table summary="This table lists the pages changed for the 27 November 2000 release with details of the change"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Topic No</th>
<th scope="col">Topic Title</th>
<th scope="col">Details</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1.1.C.215</td>
<td>Company - public &amp; private</td>
<td>Amended definition of a company and private company.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.C.330</td>
<td>Continuing inability to work (CITW) (DSP, SA)</td>
<td>Removed references to SA.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.P.90</td>
<td>Part-time employment (DSP)</td>
<td>Updated definition.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.T.70</td>
<td>Temporary incapacity for work (NSA, SA)</td>
<td>Removed references to SA.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.S.200</td>
<td>Social security entitlement</td>
<td>Removed reference to partner allowance.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.S.430</td>
<td>Supported employment (DSP)</td>
<td>Removed references to SA.</td>
</tr><tr><td>2.2.1.10</td>
<td>General Provisions for Verifying POI</td>
<td>Referred POI for children to the Family Assistance Guide.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.1.2.60</td>
<td>Other Waiting Periods for NSA &amp; YA</td>
<td>Clarified industrial action exclusion period.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.1.4.10</td>
<td>Situations that Constitute Imprisonment</td>
<td>Updated information on imprisonment.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.1.4.20</td>
<td>Payments during Periods of Imprisonment</td>
<td>Updated information on payments during periods of imprisonment.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.1.4.50</td>
<td>Reviews - Customer Undertaking Rehabilitation</td>
<td>Updated information on a course of rehabilitation.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.2.20</td>
<td>Situations Involving Industrial Action</td>
<td>Clarified industrial action exclusion period.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.5.30</td>
<td>Unreasonable to Live at Home &amp; YA</td>
<td>Added a reference to crisis payment and a link to 3.7.4.20 Qualification for CrP.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.6.40</td>
<td>Away from home rate of YA and bypassing local schools</td>
<td>Added text on students with special talents bypassing local schools.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.7</td>
<td>Away from Home Rate of YA &amp; Bypassing Local Schools</td>
<td>Included additional information on bypassing local schools and students with special talents.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.3.2.10</td>
<td>Qualification for MAA after 1 July 1996</td>
<td>Widow Allowance to qualification criteria table. Act reference 666 YBA (3) added.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.4.1.10</td>
<td>Qualification for Age Seniors &amp; Means Test</td>
<td>Deleted references to DVA pensions.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.5.1.130</td>
<td>Supplementary Benefits and Assistance for PP recipients</td>
<td>Included additional information in example under other departmental benefits - benefit PP (partnered) customers.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.1.10</td>
<td>Qualification for DSP</td>
<td>Updated qualification criteria.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.1.20</td>
<td>Qualification for DSP during employment</td>
<td>
<p>Updated overview.</p>
<p>Updated Competitive, Employment, Training &amp; Placement.</p>
<p>Updated Supported Wage System.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.2.70</td>
<td>Assessment of Continuing Inability to Work</td>
<td>
<p>Corrected error in second paragraph on Literacy, numeracy &amp; language.</p>
<p>"Other non - medical influence, should NOT be taken into account."</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.2.80</td>
<td>Determining Continuing Inability to Work using WATS</td>
<td>Included a link to 5.6.3. Use of WATs for DSP purposes.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.2.200</td>
<td>DSP customers with less than 10 years residence</td>
<td>Updated information about customers with severe congenital abnormalities.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.5.30</td>
<td>Participation of SA Recipients in Rehabilitation Programs</td>
<td>Updated qualification during a rehabilitation program.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.6.10</td>
<td>Qualification for MOB</td>
<td>Updated MOB qualifications to reflect the FaCS Amendment Bill No 1, 2000.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.6.20</td>
<td>Payability of MOB</td>
<td>Inserted a paragraph on customers receiving a GST-free car.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.6.50</td>
<td>Assessment of Other Criteria for MOB</td>
<td>
<p>Inserted a paragraph on: Job search activities under an agreement between Centrelink and a service provider funded by DEWRSB.</p>
<p>Deleted, Activity plan developed by a disability panel.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.2.30</td>
<td>SpB for Customers from New Zealand</td>
<td>Topic rewritten to reflect updated NZ agreement.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.8.1.60</td>
<td>Payments that may be treated as rent</td>
<td>
<p>Changed maintenance payments to child support maintenance payments.</p>
<p>Clarified RA eligibility for Commonwealth funded care facilities.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.8.3.20</td>
<td>PES qualifying study for tertiary students</td>
<td>
<p>Changed workload to study load.</p>
<p>Added additional information about continuing/non continuing students.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.8.3.30</td>
<td>PES and secondary students</td>
<td>Included information about special school students.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.8.3.90</td>
<td>Payability of PES</td>
<td>Inserted information about newly arrived resident's waiting period and exemptions.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.8.3.120</td>
<td>Termination of PES</td>
<td>
<p>Renamed title to Variation and Termination of PES.</p>
<p>Inserted information about date of event and date of effect of rate variations.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.8.10.70</td>
<td>Bereavement Payments for CPS Recipients</td>
<td>Referred to 5.1 for current rates.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.1.20</td>
<td>Determining the rate of income for pensions</td>
<td>Updated section on apportioning lump sums.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.2.31</td>
<td>Other Income Exempt from Assessment - Specifically Approved</td>
<td>Added Barter Jobs Australia Incorporated to list of Approved exchange trading systems.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.3.60</td>
<td>Deferred income, salary sacrifice &amp; fringe benefits</td>
<td>Included a paragraph on fringe benefits - declaration and debts.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.4.10</td>
<td>Application of the Income Maintenance Period (IMP)</td>
<td>Inserted an example on calculating the length of the IMP.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.6.10</td>
<td>Income From Overseas Pensions</td>
<td>Added US pensions to summary. Included an example of blocked overseas pensions. Further details provided on termination of UK agreement.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.9</td>
<td>Income from other sources</td>
<td>Changed title of 4.3.9.30 to Income from personal injury insurance schemes.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.9.30</td>
<td>Income from sickness and accident policy payments</td>
<td>
<p>Included a paragraph on disability pensions paid from superannuation funds.</p>
<p>Included a paragraph on salary continuance payments.</p>
<p>Included a paragraph on trauma insurance.</p>
<p>Deleted reference to payment after SA.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.9.70</td>
<td>Income From Private Annuities &amp; Overseas Income Streams</td>
<td>Clarified assessment of overseas income streams.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.6.2.20</td>
<td>Assessing exemption for irrecoverable loans and debts</td>
<td>Moved contents to 4.6.5.60 Assessing Loans &amp; Guarantor Arrangements.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.6.4.70</td>
<td>Granny Flats - Property Transfers always accepted as reasonable</td>
<td>Amended paragraph where customer provides funds for construction of granny flat to alert readers to treatment where customer pays more than 10% above the cost.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.6.5.60</td>
<td>Assessing loans &amp; Guarantor arrangements</td>
<td>Added information from 4.6.2.20 and topic rewritten.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.6.6.30</td>
<td>Encumbrances and loans against assets</td>
<td>Included an explanation on collateral security.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.7.1.80</td>
<td>Assessment of assets for partnerships</td>
<td>Amended 2.5 hectares to 2 hectares of allowable private land.</td>
</tr><tr><td>5.1.5.10</td>
<td>DSP - Current rates</td>
<td>Updated rates.</td>
</tr><tr><td>5.1.5.40</td>
<td>MOB - Current rates</td>
<td>Updated rates.</td>
</tr><tr><td>5.2.1.50</td>
<td>Youth Related Payments - July 1986 to Present Date</td>
<td>Update of YA rates.</td>
</tr><tr><td>8.1.4.40</td>
<td>DOP &amp; Parenting - Documentation Required</td>
<td>Added paragraph regarding POI documentation required for Parenting Payment.</td>
</tr></tbody></table><h2 id="30october2000">Guide to Social Security Law Update 1449G # Date 30 October 2000</h2>
<table summary="This table lists the pages changed for the 30 October 2000 release with details of the change"><caption>Corrections and Improvements</caption>
<thead><tr><th scope="col">Topic No</th>
<th scope="col">Topic Title</th>
<th scope="col">Details</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Acronym List</td>
<td> </td>
<td>
<p>Added Rural Australia Medical Undergraduate Scholarship Scheme (RAMUSS).</p>
<p>Corrected VECS to VCES Veterans' Children Education Scheme.</p>
<p>Added Transport Accident Act 1986 (Vic) - TAA.</p>
<p>Added Transport Accident Commission (Vic) - TAC.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.E.130</td>
<td>Entry Contribution</td>
<td>Clarified the difference between an entry contribution and other payments made by retirement village residents.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.L.100</td>
<td>Long term Income Support</td>
<td>Paragraph added to elaborate that being a Long term Income Support Student does not necessarily mean that a student is independent for YA.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.M.150</td>
<td>Ministers of Religion</td>
<td>
