<p>3.5.8.10</p>
<p>3.5.8.40</p>
<p>3.5.8.50</p>
<p>5.1.4.60</p>
<p>6.2.4.90</p>
<p>6.2.4.110</p>
</td>
<td>
<p>The DOP material in the Guide is being changed to reflect changes to the definition of a double orphan child and the introduction of an additional component of DOP. DOP will now be paid for double orphan children whose only living parent is on remand and charged with an offence punishable by imprisonment for ten years or more. An additional component of DOP will now be paid for children who became double orphans on or after 1/7/98 and the rate of family assistance paid to the current family in respect of the child is less than the rate of family assistance paid in respect of the child in their original family.</p>
<p>The changes will include creating a new topic called 5.1.4.70 DOP - Additional Component. This topic will explain how the additional component is calculated.</p>
</td>
